<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 24 at 9:48PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>Fog, locally dense near the headwaters of the Missouri River,
will persist through Monday morning. While most locations will see
visibilities to as low as one to three miles where fog is
occurring, travelers on I-90 in Western Gallatin County near the
Missouri Headwaters should be prepared for visibilities to as low
as one-quarter of a mile.
Be prepared for changing conditions over short distances. Slow
down and allow extra time to reach your destination. If driving
through fog, use your low beam headlights. Additionally, with
temperatures below freezing some surfaces may become slippery,
especially bridges and overpasses.</description>
